{"id":"ammi","term":"Ammi","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>My people, a name given by Jehovah to the people of Israel (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hosea 2:1\">Hos. 2:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hosea 2:23\">23</a>. Comp. 1:9; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 16:8\">Ezek. 16:8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 9:25\">Rom. 9:25</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 9:26\">26</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 2:10\">1 Pet. 2:10</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Hosea 2:1","Hosea 2:23","Ezekiel 16:8","Romans 9:25","Romans 9:26","1 Peter 2:10"]}